greenhouse_gases = greenhouse_gases[["country", "year", "co2", "co2_per_capita"]]

greenhouse_gases = greenhouse_gases.dropna()
greenhouse_gases = greenhouse_gases.rename(columns={"country": "Country", "year": "Year", "co2": "CO2", "co2_per_capita": "CO2 Per Capita"})

Creating Combined Tables¶

replacing country names according to folium for future mapping

Now going to combine the tables. I am keeping data from all columns as long as the Country and ISO Code match so there will be early years without population and co2 and there will be later years without yearly avg temp

In [45]:
temps_and_gases = pd.merge(global_temp, greenhouse_gases, how="outer", on=["Country", "Year"])
temps_and_gases = temps_and_gases[pd.notnull(temps_and_gases["Temperature"])]

Adding Country-Continent Mapping and Color-Continent Mapping¶

first adding continents issue with netherland antilles (ANT) so we replace it with BES (Bonaire) and combine data because bonaire is part of netherland antilles and now we can assign it a continent. once it is assigned, we change the ISO code back to the original code

going to do distribution for each continent

i want to see how much the temperature has changed by in each country since 1889 to 2013. using 1889 because it is the earliest year that has temperatures for all the countries

used: https://towardsdatascience.com/creating-a-simple-folium-map-covid-19-worldwide-total-case-a0a1429c6e7c

In [54]:
countries = global_temp["Country"].unique()
country_temp_change = pd.DataFrame(countries, columns=["Country"])
temp_change = list()
for country in countries:
    temp_1901 = global_temp.loc[(global_temp["Year"] == 1901) & (global_temp["Country"] == country), "Temperature"].iloc[0]
    temp_2021 = global_temp.loc[(global_temp["Year"] == 2021) & (global_temp["Country"] == country), "Temperature"].iloc[0]
    temp_change.append(temp_2021 - temp_1901)
country_temp_change["Temperature Change"] = temp_change
country_temp_change.head()
Out[54]:

1 Armenia 1.15

4 Brunei 0.54

In [56]:
map_osm = folium.Map(location=[0, 0], zoom_start=2)

cp = folium.Choropleth(
    geo_data=country_shapes,
    name='choropleth temperatures',
    data=country_temp_change,
    columns=["Country", "Temperature Change"],
    key_on='feature.properties.name',
    fill_color='RdPu',
    nan_fill_color='white'
).add_to(map_osm)


folium.GeoJsonTooltip(['name'], ['Country:']).add_to(cp.geojson)

folium.LayerControl().add_to(map_osm)

temp_change_per_continent = list()

for continent in continents:
    continent_df = country_temp_change[country_temp_change["Continent"] == continent].copy()
    continent_df = continent_df["Temperature Change"].to_numpy()
    temp_change_per_continent.append(continent_df)

plt.boxplot(temp_change_per_continent, vert=False, meanline=True, showmeans=True);
plt.yticks([1, 2, 3, 4, 5], ['Africa', 'Asia', 'Europe', 'Oceania', 'Americas'])
plt.xlabel("Temperature Change")
plt.ylabel("Continent")
plt.title("Temperature Change across Continents from 1901 to 2021");
plt.gcf().set_size_inches(10, 7)

it looks like there are three outliers, what are they?

plt.boxplot defines outliers that are < q1 - 1.5 x iqr and > q3 + 1.5 * iqr

using this tutorial https://medium.datadriveninvestor.com/finding-outliers-in-dataset-using-python-efc3fce6ce32

In [59]:
outliers = pd.DataFrame()

for continent in continents:
    continent_temp_change = country_temp_change[country_temp_change["Continent"] == continent].copy()
    q1, q3 = np.percentile(continent_temp_change["Temperature Change"], [25, 75])
    iqr = q3 - q1
    lower = q1 - (1.5 * iqr)
    upper = q3 + (1.5 * iqr)
    outliers = outliers.append(continent_temp_change[(continent_temp_change["Temperature Change"] < lower) | (continent_temp_change["Temperature Change"] > upper)]);

print(outliers)

In [94]:
countries = greenhouse_gases["Country"].unique()
country_co2_change = pd.DataFrame(countries, columns=["Country"])
co2_change = list()
for country in countries:
    num_years = len(greenhouse_gases.loc[(greenhouse_gases["Country"] == country), "CO2"])
    co2_early = greenhouse_gases.loc[(greenhouse_gases["Country"] == country), "CO2"].iloc[0]
    co2_late = greenhouse_gases.loc[(greenhouse_gases["Country"] == country), "CO2"].iloc[-1]
    co2_change.append((co2_late - co2_early) / num_years)                     
country_co2_change["CO2 Change"] = co2_change
country_co2_change.head()
Out[94]:

1 Armenia 0.054835
